article.headline: San Francisco 72, Pepperdine 71
article.story: MALIBU, Calif. (AP) -- Danny Cavic scored a career-high 19 points and Armondo Surratt added 18 as San Francisco beat Pepperdine 72-71 on Monday. Cavic had three steals, sank four 3-pointers and went seven of 10 from the field. San Franciscos Alan Wiggins Jr. tallied nine rebounds. Late in the game, the Waves had a chance to tie at 70 but turned the ball over with 29 seconds left. Surratt then sank two free throws to put the game away for the Dons (7-11, 3-0), who have opened conference play with three wins for the first time since 1991. Chase Griffin, who hit a 3-point basket at the buzzer, and Tomas Pranciliauskas both had 12 points to lead Pepperdine (4-16, 0-4). After the Dons built a 38-36 halftime lead, Pepperdine took an eight-point lead early in the second half. But San Francisco surged back on an 11-0 run. San Francisco had 12 steals to Pepperdine's five.
